1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,800
One classroom. Every voice. One Trek.

2
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:09,800
Do not watch a slideshow.
Watch one class shape what happens next.

3
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:17,200
Open Trek Exchange.
Discover reviewed Treks, ranked and shared by the community.

4
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:26,233
Remix any Trek for your class.
Student-made Treks require teacher approval.

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,800
Now Nova joins from a student device.

6
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:41,000
Nova reacts, votes for liquid water, and explains why
ice is useful only if the crew also has energy.

7
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:50,500
The live class pulse changes as the response arrives.
The teacher sees the whole room at a glance.

8
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:57,800
The teacher can share a safe idea anonymously,
without exposing the student's identity.

9
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:01,500
Mission Control asks ClassTrek
to read the room.

10
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:10,800
GPT-5.6 combines de-identified reasoning
with sources selected for this Trek.

11
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:17,300
The proposal cannot publish itself.
The teacher checks the evidence and decides.

12
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:18,600
Approve and publish.

13
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:27,800
One click advances the canonical lesson version.
Every connected screen moves to the same next question.

14
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:37,200
Students contribute evidence. AI proposes a branch.
Software enforces safety. The teacher remains in control.

15
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:43,000
Every response is checked by classroom guardrails.
Unsafe text never reaches the public display.

16
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:52,750
Codex accelerated real-time state, recovery, structured GPT output,
safety tests, and real multi-browser verification.

17
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:56,543
Little steps. One big learning journey.
Together.
